.SKIP 1
((<INTRODUCTION))
\\
.FILL.JUST
.PARA
<PRTAID REFORMATS THE INFORMATION GIVEN AT THE PROMPTS AND PLACES
EXECUTABLE <LIST OR <PRINT STATEMENTS IN A NUMBER OF ^TEMPORARY
^COMMANDS ^FILES. ^AS EACH ^COMMAND ^FILE IS FILLED, ^THE LAST LINE WRITTEN
IS A COMMAND TO RUN THE NEXT ^COMMAND ^FILE IN SEQUENCE. ^THE LAST FILE
TO BE FILLED WILL CONTAIN A <DAY COMMAND TO SERVE AS A RECOGNIZABLE
TERMINATION TO THE USER OF HIS ^COMMANDS ^FILES. ^AFTER A ^LIST OF ^FILENAMES
HAS BEEN PROCESSED AND SPACE REMAINS IN THE ^COMMANDS ^FILES, THE PROGRAM
WILL RETURN TO THE <USERNAME PROMPT. ^A CARRIAGE RETURN TERMINATES THE 
PROGRAM AT THIS POINT OR ANOTHER <USERNAME CAN BE ENTERED (<LIST OR <PRINT
AND THE OPTIONS PREVIOUSLY SELECTED WILL REMAIN CONSTANT) AND THE 
PROGRAM WILL PROCEED TO THE <FILENAMES PROMPT.
.SKIP 1
.INDEX <PRTAID <COMMAND <DESCRIPTION
((<COMMAND <DESCRIPTION))
.PARA
